-- CBS's Showtime Network Offers Online Streaming to Its Pay-TV Subscribers
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2010-10-27T20:09:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/cbs-s-showtime-network-offers-online-streaming-to-its-pay-tv-subscribers.html
CBS Corp. ’s Showtime Networks said
it has started Showtime Anytime, a broadband video and streaming
service that will be free to subscribers.  The service gives viewers the flexibility to watch more
than 400 hours of programming wherever they are, the New York-
based cable network said today in a statement. It’s operating
now on Comcast Corp.’s Xfinity, Showtime said, and other systems
will be announced later.  How viewers access Showtime Anytime will depend on who they
use for pay TV, the company said, adding that the introduction
of Internet access from a company website will be announced
later. The service allows Showtime to put its programming on the
Web while maintaining a pay wall.  CBS fell 25 cents to $16.83 at 4:01 p.m. in New York Stock
Exchange composite  trading . The shares have gained 20 percent
this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
